<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
	<meta charset="utf-8">
	<title>Animal Trading Cards</title>
  	<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
	<script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/967968288b.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
	</head>
	<body>
	<div class="flex-zone">
	
	<!-- Card #1 -->
	<div class="container container-shadow card-okapi">
	
		<div class="card-title card-contents">
			<h2>Okapi</h2>
			<div class="card-type"><i class="fa-solid fa-horse"></i></div>
		</div>
		
		<img class="card-contents" src="okapicard.png" alt="Okapi">
		
		<div class="card-description">
			<em>In spite of their zebra-like appearance,<br> the Okapi is relative to the Giraffe.</em>
			<ul>
			<li><strong>Species Name</strong>: Okapia johnstoni</li>
			<li><strong>Habitat</strong>: Central Africa</li>
			<li><strong>Diet</strong>: Herbivorous</li>
			<li><strong>Conservation Status</strong>: Endangered</li>
			</ul>
			These visually striking mini-giraffes enjoy eating all kinds of vegetation 
			(even some poisonous varieties!) 
			across their tropical habitat using their nearly 2-feet long tongues to forage.
		</div>
          
	</div>
	<!-- Card #2 -->
	<div class="container container-shadow card-corgi">
	
		<div class="card-title card-contents">
			<h2>Corgi</h2>
			<div class="card-type"><i class="fa-solid fa-dog"></i></div>
		</div>
		
		<img class="card-contents" src="corgicard.png" alt="Corgi">
		
		<div class="card-description">
			<em>In spite of their dog-like appearance,<br> the Welsh Corgi is a loaf of bread.</em>
			<ul>
			<li><strong>Species Name</strong>: Canis lupus familiaris</li>
			<li><strong>Habitat</strong>: In Your Kitchen</li>
			<li><strong>Diet</strong>: Whatever You're Having</li>
			<li><strong>Conservation Status</strong>: Dog</li>
			</ul>
			You never suspected the baked goods you brought home
			until it started barking. Don't expect any real info in this card.
			<br><br>Seriously.
		</div>
          
	</div>
	
	</div>
	</body>
</html>